DocAttribute.Name: RelatingElement
DocAttribute.Documentation: Reference to a subtype of IfcElement that is the RelatingElement in the interference relationship. Depending on the value of ImpliedOrder the RelatingElement may carry the notion to be the element from which the interference geometry should be subtracted.

DocAttribute.Name: RelatedElement
DocAttribute.Documentation: Reference to a subtype of IfcElement that is the RelatedElement in the interference relationship. Depending on the value of ImpliedOrder the RelatedElement may carry the notion to be the element from which the interference geometry should not be subtracted.

DocAttribute.Name: InterferenceGeometry
DocAttribute.Documentation: The geometric shape representation of the interference geometry that is provided in the object coordinate system of the RelatingElement (mandatory) and in the object coordinate system of the RelatedElement (optionally).

DocAttribute.Name: InterferenceType
DocAttribute.Documentation: Optional identifier that describes the nature of the interference. Examples could include 'Clash', 'ProvisionForVoid', etc.

DocAttribute.Name: ImpliedOrder
DocAttribute.Documentation: Logical value indicating whether the interference geometry should be subtracted from the RelatingElement (if TRUE), or whether it should be either subtracted from the RelatingElement or the RelatedElement (if FALSE), or whether no indication can be provided (if UNKNOWN).

DocWhereRule.Name: NotSelfReference
DocWhereRule.Documentation: The instance of the RelatingElement shall not be the same instance as the RelatedElement.
